#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added custom third-party model API provider feature, added CherryIN as system default provider;
- Improved document upload experience when editing knowledge base;
- Fixed issue where errors would duplicate when adding online models;
- Added Perplexity as search provider;
- Added support for Qwen Image generation and Google's official image generation models;
- Adapted iOS 26 liquid glass effect;
- Fixed other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major updates:
- Adapted to the latest large models such as GLM4.5, Kimi K2, GPT5;
- Fixed other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added planning execution feature: for non-thinking models, selecting planning execution will let the model think first, then execute tasks based on the plan;
- Supported reasoning length settings for certain reasoning models;
- Updated compatibility with latest models such as DeepSeek R1 and Claude 4.0;
- Optimized parts of the UI and features to improve smoothness, and fixed other known bugs and issues.

#### 🚀 Main Updates:
- Added support for Qwen’s full-modal model Omni and its audio output, including automatic saving after voice message generation, as well as playback controls like pause, speed adjustment, seek, and duration display;
- Introduced scientific text mode for rendering mathematical formulas;
- Optimized the output format of Thought Mode for a smoother experience;
- Agent now supports re-editing the base model, with more flexible selection and support for copying system-provided agents;
- Added default model sorting button, which restores the default model order when clicked in edit mode;
- Optimized parts of the interface and functionality, and fixed other known bugs and issues;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Optimized the Knowledge Backpack feature: added a writing tool that allows supported models to draft knowledge documents. Improved knowledge chunk retrieval strategies by introducing a new mechanism for more accurate and faster searches;
- Updated to the latest models such as Qwen3 and Baidu 4.5Turbo, with support for the Qwen3 inference toggle;
- Enhanced web search capabilities: added arXiv literature search tool and an online file parsing tool. Supported models can now autonomously search for papers and analyze detailed content based on provided paper links;
- Supported persistent saving of chat translation results to avoid redundant translations;
- Supported display of inference time and reference count;
- Optimized parts of the interface and functionality, and fixed other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Enhanced memory features: now supports memory updates and injections, improving recall performance;
- UI and feature refinements, along with fixes for known issues and bugs.

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added a Health Tool in chat: When using supported models, you can now query your activity, energy, and nutrition data. Models can also analyze your diet and generate nutrition cards for easy storage in the system’s Health app;
- Weather query feature added to the Map Tool;
- Code Tool now supports running Python code;
- Knowledge Backpack introduces proactive retrieval: supported models will now proactively search the backpack when needed. More parameter settings are now available for customization;
- UI and functionality optimizations, along with various bug fixes.

#### 🚀 Main Updates:
- Introduced a new Web Tool in chat: supported models can now generate HTML code to implement specific tools or display custom content;
- Added proactive online search: when enabled, supported models will automatically retrieve information from the internet when needed;
- Optimized parts of the UI and features, and fixed other known issues and bugs.

#### 🚀 Main Updates:
- Calendar tool added in chat: supported models can now intelligently query calendar events and reminders, and are allowed to write events/reminders directly;
- Google Maps engine introduced in the map tool, configurable as needed;
- UI and feature optimizations, along with fixes for known bugs and issues;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Introduced Amap (Gaode) map engine with configurable options;
- Updated support for GPT-4.1, new Zhipu models, and more;
- Optimized some UI and features, and fixed other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Main Updates:
- Map feature now supports route planning. When chatting with supported models, the model can proactively help plan driving, public transit, or walking routes;
- Optimized parts of the interface and functionality, and fixed other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Chat conversations now support map display! When chatting with supported models, geographic questions will result in an intuitive map view. You can ask about your current location, search for nearby places based on specific locations, select a location, view directions with one click, and switch to satellite map view;
- UI and feature improvements, along with fixes for other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added support for Gitee AI API services, and updated to include the latest models such as Baidu X1 and Grok 3;
- Improved parts of the UI and functionality, and fixed other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added support for selecting voice models, currently supporting Siri, OpenAI, and SiliconCloud voices;
- Optimized some interfaces and features, and fixed other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Optimized file upload and parsing: now supports uploading multiple files and conversations simultaneously;
- Added translation dictionary feature: customize translation pairs for more personalized translation in real-time usage;
- Improved some UI and features, and fixed other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added support for reverse prompts and canvas size settings in image generation models (only applicable to supported models); optimized chat interface performance;
- Enabled fast downloads for more local models and allowed users to upload GGUF-format files to use local models;
- Optimized some UI elements and features; fixed other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added support for customizing text and visual optimization models;
- Added setting for customizing the number of search results;
- Added ability to manually add image generation models compatible with OpenAI format;
- Improved several UI components and functionalities, and fixed known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Main Updates:
- Fixed compatibility issues with local models on the 18.4 system, optimized local model performance, and added downloadable DeepSeek distilled model and Llama model; local models can now also perform inference. Local models now also support adjustments for parameters such as temperature, cumulative probability, and maximum response length.
- Added support for xAI's image generation model;
- Introduced a memory archive feature. When conversing with supported models (marked with “Tools” in the model list), the model will automatically remember certain important information and recall it when needed to enhance the conversation experience. You can view and manage memory archive contents in the settings;
- Optimized certain interfaces and functionalities, and fixed other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added support for text-to-image generation models. You can now select an image generation model in chat and generate images based on prompts. Currently supports OpenAI, Alibaba Wanxian, Zhipu AI, and SiliconFlow, with two free built-in trial models. Context-aware prompt optimization is supported.
- Added support for the Brave search engine;
- Optimized parts of the UI and features, and fixed other known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added custom system messages for multi-turn conversations, enhancing flexibility and interactivity;
- Improved intent prediction for visual functions, making responses more precise;
- Prompt library now supports long-press to reorder, added search by prompt title, and supports Pinyin search;
- Integrated Tencent Hunyuan T1 and OpenAI o1-Pro models;
- Optimized some UI elements and functionalities, and fixed known issues and bugs.

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added a temporary chat button. Chat information will be automatically deleted after exiting temporary chat;
- Optimized some interfaces and functionalities, and fixed other known issues and bugs.

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added chat history export feature, supporting both plain text files (.txt) for easier sharing and JSON (.json) format for structured content export. The JSON format also supports OpenAI multimodal format with base64 image data export;
- Added chat history import feature, allowing one-click restoration of complete conversations using JSON files that match the export format, including base64 image data restoration;
- Introduced a message limit adjustment feature with automatic per-chat saving. The maximum response length setting is now also saved per chat;
- Optimized various UI elements and functionalities, and fixed other known issues and bugs.

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- The 'Prompt Library' feature is now available! You can pre-edit commonly used prompts in settings and quickly apply them in chats by clicking. Note that the prompt content will be added before your input. Local models also support the 'Prompt Library';
- Local models now support local file uploads, allowing you to process files without an internet connection;
- Added support for Baidu Wenxin series models, iFlytek Spark series models, and Perplexity series models;
- Introduced Hanlin preset models, making AI intelligence accessible for beginners;
- Optimized some UI elements and functionalities, and fixed other known issues and bugs.

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Optimized the interaction when first entering the app, guiding users to set up API keys for normal use;
- Added a 'Sync Model List' button in the model list to quickly synchronize the global model list;
- Improved the search function at the top of the list, supporting highlighted search results, optimized Pinyin search, and enabling direct navigation to found chat records;
- Instant summary function now supports web page content summarization;
- Optimized some interfaces and functions, and fixed other known issues and bugs.

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Fixed the issue where the camera could not be flipped;
- Optimized some interfaces and functionalities, and fixed other known issues and bugs.

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Support for adding images to the chat input box by pasting;
- Optimize file parsing function and expand the supported file types, including: Plain Text (TXT), Markdown (MD), Word Document (DOCX), PowerPoint Presentation (PPTX), PDF files (PDF), Excel spreadsheets (XLSX), comma-separated value files (CSV), Python code files (PY), JSON files (JSON), log files (LOG) and HTML files (HTML). 
- Optimize the style of the bottom status bar, fix possible non-display issues; 
- Optimize some interfaces and functions, fix known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- A completely upgraded online search feature, supporting configuration options for selecting search engines. Now supports Bocha AI (same as DeepSeeek), Bocha AI International Version (LangSearch), EXA AI, Tavily, and Zhipu Huazhang, with support for enabling bilingual searches;
- Optimized search functionality and performance, improved understanding of search context and image search capabilities;
- Optimize chat history loading performance and support pull-to-load. Add an automatic group chat naming feature that automatically names the chat when there are 5 effective messages.
- Improved certain interfaces and functionalities, fixed known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Optimized visual flash functionality, supporting selfie lighting and improved zoom smoothness;
- Improved various UI elements and functions, and fixed known issues and bugs;
- Initial adaptation of Chinese and English software interfaces, as well as Chinese and English prompts, questions, and answers.

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added haptic feedback for button presses and AI outputs, with customizable toggles for feedback during text generation;
- Enhanced visual functions: supports selecting photos from the album, added camera flip, flash, and image saving features; for Pro models, supports a wider zoom range and a new text selection button;
- Enabled model providers to customize activation; when disabled, their models will be hidden from both the overall model list and group chat model lists;
- Introduced search functionality for group chat model lists, including text and pinyin search;
- Updated the new logo for Zhipu, optimized performance, improved some UI and functions, and fixed known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Introduced instant translation, text refinement, and summarization features for a quick AI experience, eliminating concerns over data redundancy and messy chats. Instant translation supports 19 languages/dialects, instant refinement offers 12 styles, 9 formats, and 3 length options with customizable requirements, and instant summarization provides concise summaries of long texts;
- Optimized document upload and image processing speeds for text models;
- Adapted for the StepStar series models;
- Improved color schemes and various UI functions, and fixed known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added online search functionality for multi-modal models that can perform web searches based on image content; if multiple images are provided, only the first is used, theoretically enabling online search for all models;
- Added image analysis for text models so that language models can also accept image uploads (note: results may not be as effective as multi-modal models and loading times may increase);
- Enhanced the visual interface to display follow-up questions;
- Added support for Tencent Hunyuan's large model;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Introduced download, management, and usage of local models;
- Supported quick access to the visual interface via shortcut commands;
- Added user information input to better personalize chats;
- Optimized the default model selection logic when opening a group chat interface;
- Improved various UI elements and functions, and fixed known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Launched a new visual color scheme;
- Fixed an issue where audio playback paused unexpectedly when the app started;
- Improved some UI elements and fixed known issues and bugs;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Optimized the chat interface to enhance fluidity and improve user experience;
- Introduced online search functionality with reference materials, supporting all pure text models;
- Adapted for the ZeroOne series models;
- Fixed other known issues and bugs to improve stability;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Enhanced visual module interactions and UI, and added follow-up chat functionality;
- Added support for the Claude flagship model;
- Optimized certain data processing logics to improve performance;
- Fixed other known issues and bugs to enhance stability;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Added model list and selection options, supporting synchronization of model changes across all group chats;
- Redesigned the main chat interface to increase information density, better suit chat scenarios, optimize splash screen issues, support pull-to-refresh, and enable pinyin search for group chat names;
- Supported Kimi, xAI, and local network models, allowing local models to run on computers via Olama or LM Studio with similar mobile effects, and added a new access point setting for ByteDoubao models;
- Introduced a new visual interface for quick access to visual capabilities;
- Fixed other known issues and bugs, optimized performance, and improved stability;

#### 🚀 Major Updates:
- Corrected pricing metrics:
  1. ¥0: Free
  2. Below ¥0.001 per thousand tokens: Cheap
  3. ¥0.001 - ¥0.006 per thousand tokens: Moderate
  4. ¥0.006 per thousand tokens and above: Expensive
  - Note: Billing is calculated separately for input (50%) and output (50%);
- Optimized certain UI interactions, added time display, and enabled swipe-to-go-back on the left-side interface;
- Updated support for certain models, which will be effective in new chats while existing chats continue to support previous models;
- Fixed known issues and bugs, optimized performance, and improved stability;

#### 🚀 Key Features:
- Multi-model group chat: Supports mainstream models from platforms such as Zhipu Qingyan, Tongyi Qianwen, ByteDoubao, DeepSeek, SiliconCloud, OpenAI (Beta), and Google Gemini (Beta), with support for custom APIs;
- Multi-modal input: Supports text input, image upload, file upload, and web search according to different models;
- Convenient multi-line text input: Supports multi-line text input, auto-optimized prompts, quick text translation, and intelligent text recognition;
- Various model response presentation and interaction methods: Supports Markdown parsing, reasoning chain display, quick copy, text selection, smart translation, Siri reading, and re-requesting;
- Diverse personalization options: Supports custom group chat names, symbols, and colors, as well as defining different model displays and orders for different group chats;
- Management of multiple conversations: Supports creating multiple group chats, quick search of group chat names and contents, and pinning group chats.

👏 Welcome to use our app. Please contact the developer if you encounter any issues.
